*Code BREAKING - Just PUBLIC Keys to Break

Code BREAKING - Just PUBLIC Keys to Break

***FIRST START WITH "Post before Friday October 25th - midnight to be eligible for full credit on the project." " (recommended due date Oct. 25th, Oct. 28th if needed.
The "Post before Friday October 25th" must be completed by Oct. 28th to get full credit on the project) " before posting to this code breaking thread ***
THIS, Code Breaking, thread must be done before you complete your project.

Post Codes with Just Public Keys (Code Breaking)

When you are ready, post your codes in the follow-ups and then use the "reply" to respond in code.
>>>>Use the same method from the first thread of "follow up" for new codes to break, and "replies" when breaking codes.<<<
  • You may MAKE comments in text about the message or runtime to break the code about the messages in these threads, but please don't translate the exact messages here .
  • In this thread, just post the Public keys - *this is where I will check that you have done this part of the project.*

  • In your project you can post the private keys you have found and the exact translations. In your project , copy the code you break and share the translation in your project.  For example "I broke Joe's code [1,2,3,5], it says "I'm getting an A!"




****************************************************************
PLEASE KEEP KEYS UNDER 12 DIGITS LONG

- If you want to try really long keys, start a new thread FOR CHALLENGES and be prepared to crash your computer!

****************************************************************


Here are some messages from last semester while we wait for more to join us.


You can actually do them all with the standard factorize function we are given, but the time it takes to do so increases noticeably so I thought this would be a good one for people to practice on while getting their standard and more advanced factorize functions working.

Advanced code breaking - if AFTER posting to messages here (and in the 1st thread) you want to focus on code breaking for your custom feature, you may start your own thread for a particularly clever/advanced/some kind of twist codes. But please start on this thread with basic code break using our RSA method first.
